Source: memguard
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: sevheng <sevheng@users.noreply.github.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 12), cargo, rustc
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/sevheng/memguard

Package: memguard
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, systemd
Description: Linux desktop memory pressure daemon
 memguard monitors system memory pressure and protects the active desktop shell
 and foreground application by freezing or killing background cgroups before the
 OOM killer is triggered.

Package: memguard-system-tune
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, systemd, util-linux
Recommends: ananicy-cpp
Description: Static system tuning for memguard desktops
 One-time system tuning helper for low-end desktops using memguard. Sets the
 I/O scheduler to bfq, enables ananicy-cpp, configures zram, runs fstrim, and
 adds noatime to fstab.
